Buffalo City Metro has missed a deadline to complete and deliver 1137 RDP houses for hundreds of disadvantaged families from Fynbos, East Bank and Ndancama informal settlements. As a result, it has cost the metro more than R13.4-million in extra costs for time extensions and for contractors lost time.The project awarded to Motheo and Mpumalanga JV construction companies started in 2014 and formed part of BCM s eradication of shacks programme.READ MORE IN THE DISPATCH TODAY&#8230;&nbsp;